				\begin{document} $$I=\frac{n\sum\nolimits_{i,j}W_{ij}\left(x_{i}-\overline{x}\right)\left(x_{j}-\overline{x}\right)}{\sum\nolimits_{i,j}W_{ij}\sum\nolimits_{i}(x_{i}-\overline{x})^{2}}, $$ \end{document}I=n∑i,jWijxi−x¯xj−x¯∑i,jWij∑i(xi−x¯)2, where n is the number of spatial units indexed by i and j; xi is the variable of interest in spatial unit i; \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
				\usepackage{amsfonts} 
				\usepackage{amssymb} 
				\usepackage{amsbsy}
