				\begin{document}$\overline {x}$\end{document}x¯ is the mean of x; wij is the spatial weight of relationship between units i and j. The above formula can provide an index of dispersion from -1 to +1, corresponding to maximum negative and positive autocorrelation, respectively [15].

First, LISA was used to identify the localized clustering with specific districts. For the spatial unit i, LISA is computed as [16] 
\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
